args:
They both disappeared into that rock.
Clearly, any paradise preached by a shady
character like him is... No. Right now,
I've other matters to deal with.
Finally, a chance to put my training for\nopening secret doors to use! In I go...
There are no delays in preparation,\nI trust?
None, Father. The monster maintenance\nhas been completed as you commanded.
We must eliminate all outsiders who\nwould threaten us. This is for the sake\nof our paradise. Understand?
All shall be as you will it, Father.
So many monsters!\nAnd those townspeople there must all be...
No. Whatever the situation may be,\nmy duty is clear. After all...
I expect great things from you.
She's the first to expect great things\nfrom me, and I will not let her down.\nSigil, unleash!
All of you, surrender immediately and put\nyour hands in the air!
I'm sorry it had to come to this, Bishop\nRoalta. I heard a great many compliments\nabout you from the people of your town.
But is what I see here the truth of you?\nThese monsters are all under your\ncontrol, yes?
There can be no dissembling your way out\nof this; a normal bishop would never be in\nsuch a place at this hour.

A Sigil? Then you ARE an apostle!
Bah! Your kind is no better than a dog
that comes running whenever your
angel master calls!
If you are truly such, it is all the more\nreason I cannot permit you to live.\nI fear the time for subtlety is past.

You took an attack from my strongest,
yet still draw breath? You are an apostle
indeed—a fact I should have known after
you drove my monsters hence twice!
Then that means the monsters in town\nand the cave were BOTH your doing?!

Yes. All who come to ferret out the secrets
of Muskov are to be eaten by monsters—
for no sacrifice is too dear if it permits
our paradise to continue!

As an apostle, even your corpse carries
significant value; the armed forces of the
Osborne Principality have already sworn
to meet any price in exchange for it!
Compared to the pittance I earn selling\nsmall bits of information on the Church,\nit will be an incomparable amount!
So you ARE the informant! Aaaugh!
No! It knocked my bow away!
Aaah ha ha ha! It seems that the army's\ntechnological prowess has surpassed the\nsacramental powers of the Church!
And apostle or no, without your weapon,\nyou are as good as dead.

Ah, but this monster is wondrous!
The day of my rise to papal status is close
at hand indeed—I shall certainly have to
thank the military.
The Goddess will never stand\nfor such a thing...
Oh, but she shall—for only you have\ngleaned my secrets, and your pitiful life\nends here. ...Destroy her, Alpha!
But do it quickly, that she may go\npeacefully into the arms of the Goddess.
